args: Hmm. Now I get itâ€”this is where\nthat move from earlier pays off.
Aurien? How'd you get in here?!
Oh, I just spun a plausible yarn to convince\nthis hut's owner to part with a spare key.
Hey! My UNCLE owns this hut!
Heh. Surprised at my effectiveness?\nMy way with words has many uses,\nincluding winning all manner of duels.

Words can lead a foe to mistakes,
which can lead to great upsets.
They are even powerful enough
to let you defeat Leif at chess!
What are you trying to say?
I'm saying you must be willing\nto do whatever it takes to win.
At some point, everyone faces a battle\nthey can't afford to loseâ€”a battle worth\nstaking their very future on.
Some may call your passion a mere game,\nbut to you it is something to which you\nhave chosen to dedicate your entire youth.
I can teach you the art of words\nif you like. What say you?
Nope. Sorry, but I don't want to rely\non something like that.
Games are special to me because they're\nthe one thing I put my heart and soul into.
And that's why I want to beat Leif with\nmy own skill!
Impressive! And here I thought you would\nstill be in shock over your defeat.
Yeah, it's all thanks to Sam.
Sam remembers everything about\nmy match with Leif, which let me\nanalyze why I lost in the first place.
It sucks to admit, but Leif was right:\nI was entirely focused on offense\nat the expense of any defense.
But now I've spent ages studying defensive\nmoves so I won't make the same mistake!
Why are you laughing?! I'm serious, gosh!
My apologies. Seeing the light of youth\njust brought me such great joy.
It takes a good deal of strength to admit\nyour shortcomings and work to fix them.
I just don't wanna lose again. That's all.
There's no need for false modesty.\nYour way of thinking has true class,\nand I respect that.
So permit me to give you my help in a\nmore legitimate way: You may test all the\ndefensive skills you have learned on me.
And so Eugene set about training with Aurien\nfor the next several days...
Is it true that Eugene came back,\nPrince {player_name}?!
Yes, and he just challenged\nLeif to a rematch!
Oh man! I gotta round up everybody\nand make him a cheering section!
The air is so tense I could cut\nthrough it with my blade.
I think we should keep quiet\nand let him concentrate.
Then let's cheer him on in our minds!
(My hands won't stop sweating!\nOkay, Eugene, calm down.)
(If I just focus on what's in front of me,\nI'll be defeated like last time. I need to\ntake in the entire board instead...)
I will take your grassland warrior\nwith my sellsword.
And I'll move my stone trebuchet\nto the center!
An excellent move; you fend off my\noffensive while advancing your own.
I've never seen him think about a move for\nso long before. Is he actually cornered?
(Oh man, that's brilliant!\nThere go all my plans...)
Leif is moving in for the kill! Is Eugene\ngoing to be able to handle this?
(Should I withdraw and regroup,\nor press forward...?)
(Dang it, I'm getting so tired, my eyes\nare going blurry. Maybe I should just\nwager everything on a surprise attack.)
(No, that's what cost me the match\nlast time... Think, Eugene! Think!)
(Wait. There's one spot in his formation\nthat's less well defended than the rest.\nIf I take advantage of that, I could...win?)
All right. I'm moving my woodland archer\nforward to take your sellsword.
You fell for the lure I placed before you.\nPerhaps the promise of respite was too\ntempting, and your concentration lapsed.
I will take advantage of the opening\nyour woodland archer left to strike\nwith my stone trebuchet.
That is checkmate. Still, I commend you\non how much you've improved in such a\nshort time. We fought as equals today.
The match was decided by our mental\nstamina. Had yours been greater,\nit may have ended very differently.
Yeah, but I STILL lostâ€”and that's after I\ntrained forever! I'm no good at this...
That's not true! Heck, I bet\nyou'll totally win next time!
Oh my gosh. Were you guys all\nwatching me this entire time?
How can you cheer me on after all\nthe jerk things I said to you?
What, that? Pffft! Water under the bridge!
Cheering friends on is what friends do!
Yeeeees? Don't tell me I'm the only one\nwho thinks this is a friendship.
Heh heh... N-no, of course not.\nF-friends it is, then!
Um, and thanks for coming to\nsupport someone like me.
That's all the more reason I wanted\nto answer your support and win!
Now THIS is what youth is all about.
The ï¼‚normal teen youthï¼‚ I wanted is about\nfeeling incredibly pathetic and frustrated\nall the time?
Then why was I so eager to experience it?!
